# Phishing Awareness & Detection – Task 2  

## 📌 Project Overview  
This repository documents my internship project on **phishing detection and awareness**. The focus is on analyzing phishing emails, identifying technical red flags, and proposing business‑friendly defense strategies.  

## 🎯 Objectives  
- Perform forensic analysis of phishing samples.  
- Identify social engineering tactics (urgency, spoofing, typosquatting).  
- Conduct technical header inspection (SPF, DKIM, DMARC).  
- Classify risks and propose mitigation strategies.  
- Develop an awareness framework for employees.  

## 🛠️ Tools & Frameworks  
- **Google Admin Toolbox** – Messageheader Analysis.  
- **SPF/DKIM/DMARC** – Authentication checks.  
- **OWASP & MITRE ATT&CK (T1566)** – Industry frameworks for phishing classification.  

##  Key Findings  
- Attack leveraged Gmail infrastructure to bypass filters (SPF/DKIM: PASS).  
- Fraudulent sender identity masked by display name impersonation.  
- Malicious links hosted on typosquatted domains.  
- Risk level classified as **CRITICAL**.  

##  Recommendations  
- Implement **Multi‑Factor Authentication (MFA)** across portals.  
- Adopt the **Look‑Hover‑Report** awareness protocol.  
- Conduct regular **phishing simulations** for staff training.  
- Enforce **DMARC reject policy** to prevent brand spoofing.  

